bio: I work with raw pigments,mica,crushed crystals,18k gold & silver. Creating a continuous, primal healing effect filled with a ever changing movement.

These electric blues take my eye by surprise. Sometimes … I can’t believe I created them. I love working with blues because it washes away the day releasing what is not needed to have a fresh focus on hand. People ask why I always love painting with Blue sometimes I answer it this way, other times I just tell them I’m a mermaid from Atlantis 😂😘🧜‍♀️

I’m very saddened to hear about Glen Mayo Sculptor passing. He was an extremely talented artist who would beat to his own drum. When I first moved back to South Florida in 2014. I had met Mayo purely by chance and we had become friends. He gave me my first exposure in South Florida before I joined any art galleries there. I was a part of his sculpture studio and would show my works with his.  It was a beyond kind gesture on his part and the studio was truly magical. The last I heard from him was that he had left South Florida to live and work in Woodstock NY around the time I had just moved to Northern Florida. Life is truly serendipitous at times. I’m so sorry to hear of your passing yet so grateful for your friendship, time and support. RIP Mayo 🐉￼I still have all the metal arrows for that painting laying around my studio. 😭
